events.description: Thespis of Icaria becomes the first recorded actor to portray a character on stage.
events.html: • 534 BC – Thespis of Icaria becomes the first recorded actor to portray a character on stage.[1]

events.description: Conquest of Seville by Christian troops under King Ferdinand III of Castile.
events.html: • 1248 – Conquest of Seville by Christian troops under King Ferdinand III of Castile.

events.description: Seven days after being convicted of treason, Perkin Warbeck, a pretender to the throne of England, is hanged for attempting to escape from the Tower of London; his supporter John Atwater is executed with him.
events.html: • 1499 – Seven days after being convicted of treason, Perkin Warbeck, a pretender to the throne of England, is hanged for attempting to escape from the Tower of London; his supporter John Atwater is executed with him.[2]

events.description: John Milton publishes Areopagitica, a pamphlet decrying censorship.
events.html: • 1644 – John Milton publishes Areopagitica, a pamphlet decrying censorship.[3]

events.description: The start of the 1733 slave insurrection on St. John in what was then the Danish West Indies.
events.html: • 1733 – The start of the 1733 slave insurrection on St. John in what was then the Danish West Indies.

events.description: French and Poles defeat the Spanish at Battle of Tudela.
events.html: • 1808 – French and Poles defeat the Spanish at Battle of Tudela.

events.description: American Civil War: Battle of Chattanooga begins: Union forces led by General Ulysses S. Grant reinforce troops at Chattanooga, Tennessee, and counter-attack Confederate troops.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: Battle of Chattanooga begins: Union forces led by General Ulysses S. Grant reinforce troops at Chattanooga, Tennessee, and counter-attack Confederate troops.[4]

events.description: The Manchester Martyrs are hanged in Manchester, England, for killing a police officer while freeing two Irish Republican Brotherhood members from custody.
events.html: • 1867 – The Manchester Martyrs are hanged in Manchester, England, for killing a police officer while freeing two Irish Republican Brotherhood members from custody.[5]

events.description: Corrupt Tammany Hall leader William Magear Tweed (better known as Boss Tweed) is delivered to authorities in New York City after being captured in Spain.
events.html: • 1876 – Corrupt Tammany Hall leader William Magear Tweed (better known as Boss Tweed) is delivered to authorities in New York City after being captured in Spain.

events.description: King William III of the Netherlands dies without a male heir and a special law is passed to allow his daughter Princess Wilhelmina to succeed him.
events.html: • 1890 – King William III of the Netherlands dies without a male heir and a special law is passed to allow his daughter Princess Wilhelmina to succeed him.

events.description: Johan Alfred Ander becomes the last person to be executed in Sweden.
events.html: • 1910 – Johan Alfred Ander becomes the last person to be executed in Sweden.

events.description: Mexican Revolution: The last of U.S. forces withdraw from Veracruz, occupied seven months earlier in response to the Tampico Affair.
events.html: • 1914 – Mexican Revolution: The last of U.S. forces withdraw from Veracruz, occupied seven months earlier in response to the Tampico Affair.

events.description: Warren G. Harding, 29th President of the United States, signs the Willis–Campbell Act into law, prohibiting doctors from prescribing beer or liquor for medicinal purposes.
events.html: • 1921 – Warren G. Harding, 29th President of the United States, signs the Willis–Campbell Act into law, prohibiting doctors from prescribing beer or liquor for medicinal purposes.[6]

events.description: The 1923 Irish hunger strikes ends, four Irish Republicans die from starvation.
events.html: • 1923 – The 1923 Irish hunger strikes ends, four Irish Republicans die from starvation.[7]

events.description: Edwin Hubble's discovery, that the Andromeda "nebula" is actually another island galaxy far outside our own Milky Way, is first published in The New York Times.
events.html: • 1924 – Edwin Hubble's discovery, that the Andromeda "nebula" is actually another island galaxy far outside our own Milky Way, is first published in The New York Times.[8]

events.description: An Anglo-Ethiopian boundary commission in the Ogaden discovers an Italian garrison at Walwal, well within Ethiopian territory. This leads to the Abyssinia Crisis.
events.html: • 1934 – An Anglo-Ethiopian boundary commission in the Ogaden discovers an Italian garrison at Walwal, well within Ethiopian territory. This leads to the Abyssinia Crisis.

events.description: World War II: HMS Rawalpindi is sunk by the German battleships Scharnhorst and Gneisenau.
events.html: • 1939 – World War II: HMS Rawalpindi is sunk by the German battleships Scharnhorst and Gneisenau.

events.description: World War II: Romania becomes a signatory of the Tripartite Pact, officially joining the Axis powers.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Romania becomes a signatory of the Tripartite Pact, officially joining the Axis powers.

events.description: World War II: The Deutsche Opernhaus on Bismarckstraße in the Berlin neighborhood of Charlottenburg is destroyed. It will eventually be rebuilt in 1961 and be called the Deutsche Oper Berlin.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: The Deutsche Opernhaus on Bismarckstraße in the Berlin neighborhood of Charlottenburg is destroyed. It will eventually be rebuilt in 1961 and be called the Deutsche Oper Berlin.

events.description: World War II: Tarawa and Makin atolls fall to American forces.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Tarawa and Makin atolls fall to American forces.

events.description: World War II: The Lotta Svärd Movement is disbanded under the terms of the armistice treaty in Finland after the Continuation War.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Lotta Svärd Movement is disbanded under the terms of the armistice treaty in Finland after the Continuation War.[9]

events.description: French naval bombardment of Hai Phong, Vietnam, kills thousands of civilians.
events.html: • 1946 – French naval bombardment of Hai Phong, Vietnam, kills thousands of civilians.

events.description: The Cocos Islands are transferred from the control of the United Kingdom to that of Australia.
events.html: • 1955 – The Cocos Islands are transferred from the control of the United Kingdom to that of Australia.[10]

events.description: French President Charles de Gaulle declares in a speech in Strasbourg his vision for "Europe, from the Atlantic to the Urals".
events.html: • 1959 – French President Charles de Gaulle declares in a speech in Strasbourg his vision for "Europe, from the Atlantic to the Urals".

events.description: The first episode of Doctor Who (An Unearthly Child) is broadcast by the BBC, which is now the world's longest running science fiction drama.
events.html: • 1963 – The first episode of Doctor Who (An Unearthly Child) is broadcast by the BBC, which is now the world's longest running science fiction drama.[11]

events.description: Representatives of the People's Republic of China attend the United Nations, including the United Nations Security Council, for the first time.
events.html: • 1971 – Representatives of the People's Republic of China attend the United Nations, including the United Nations Security Council, for the first time.

events.description: The Soviet Union makes its final attempt at launching the N1 rocket.
events.html: • 1972 – The Soviet Union makes its final attempt at launching the N1 rocket.[12]

events.description: Sixty Ethiopian politicians, aristocrats, military officers, and other persons are executed by the provisional military government.
events.html: • 1974 – Sixty Ethiopian politicians, aristocrats, military officers, and other persons are executed by the provisional military government.[13]

events.description: Jacques Mayol is the first man to reach a depth of 100 m (330 ft) undersea without breathing equipment.
events.html: • 1976 – Jacques Mayol is the first man to reach a depth of 100 m (330 ft) undersea without breathing equipment.[14]

events.description: Cyclone kills about 1,000 people in eastern Sri Lanka.
events.html: • 1978 – Cyclone kills about 1,000 people in eastern Sri Lanka.

events.description: The Geneva Frequency Plan of 1975 goes into effect, realigning many of Europe's longwave and mediumwave broadcasting frequencies.
events.html: • 1978 – The Geneva Frequency Plan of 1975 goes into effect, realigning many of Europe's longwave and mediumwave broadcasting frequencies.[15]

events.description: The 6.9 Mw  Irpinia earthquake shakes southern Italy with a maximum Mercalli intensity of X (Extreme), killing 2,483–4,900, and injuring 7,700–8,934.
events.html: • 1980 – The 6.9 Mw  Irpinia earthquake shakes southern Italy with a maximum Mercalli intensity of X (Extreme), killing 2,483–4,900, and injuring 7,700–8,934.

events.description: Iran–Contra affair: Ronald Reagan signs the top secret National Security Decision Directive 17 (NSDD-17), giving the Central Intelligence Agency the authority to recruit and support Contra rebels in Nicaragua.
events.html: • 1981 – Iran–Contra affair: Ronald Reagan signs the top secret National Security Decision Directive 17 (NSDD-17), giving the Central Intelligence Agency the authority to recruit and support Contra rebels in Nicaragua.

events.description: Gunmen hijack EgyptAir Flight 648 en route from Athens to Cairo. When the plane lands in Malta, Egyptian commandos storm the aircraft, but 60 people die in the raid.
events.html: • 1985 – Gunmen hijack EgyptAir Flight 648 en route from Athens to Cairo. When the plane lands in Malta, Egyptian commandos storm the aircraft, but 60 people die in the raid.

events.description: Queen lead singer Freddie Mercury announces in a statement that he is HIV-positive. He dies the following day.
events.html: • 1991 – Queen lead singer Freddie Mercury announces in a statement that he is HIV-positive. He dies the following day.[16]

events.description: The first smartphone, the IBM Simon, is introduced at COMDEX in Las Vegas, Nevada.
events.html: • 1992 – The first smartphone, the IBM Simon, is introduced at COMDEX in Las Vegas, Nevada.

events.description: Ethiopian Airlines Flight 961 is hijacked, then crashes into the Indian Ocean off the coast of Comoros after running out of fuel, killing 125.
events.html: • 1996 – Ethiopian Airlines Flight 961 is hijacked, then crashes into the Indian Ocean off the coast of Comoros after running out of fuel, killing 125.

events.description: The Convention on Cybercrime is signed in Budapest, Hungary.
events.html: • 2001 – The Convention on Cybercrime is signed in Budapest, Hungary.

events.description: Space Shuttle Endeavour launches on STS-113 to the International Space Station carrying the Expedition 6 crew and the P1 truss.
events.html: • 2002 – Space Shuttle Endeavour launches on STS-113 to the International Space Station carrying the Expedition 6 crew and the P1 truss.[17]

events.description: Rose Revolution: Georgian president Eduard Shevardnadze resigns following weeks of mass protests over flawed elections.
events.html: • 2003 – Rose Revolution: Georgian president Eduard Shevardnadze resigns following weeks of mass protests over flawed elections.

events.description: The Holy Trinity Cathedral of Tbilisi, the largest religious building in Georgia, is consecrated.
events.html: • 2004 – The Holy Trinity Cathedral of Tbilisi, the largest religious building in Georgia, is consecrated.

events.description: Ellen Johnson Sirleaf is elected president of Liberia and becomes the first woman to lead an African country.
events.html: • 2005 – Ellen Johnson Sirleaf is elected president of Liberia and becomes the first woman to lead an African country.

events.description: A series of bombings kills at least 215 people and injures 257 others in Sadr City, making it the second deadliest sectarian attack since the beginning of the Iraq War in 2003.
events.html: • 2006 – A series of bombings kills at least 215 people and injures 257 others in Sadr City, making it the second deadliest sectarian attack since the beginning of the Iraq War in 2003.

events.description: MS Explorer, a cruise liner carrying 154 people, sinks in the Antarctic Ocean south of Argentina after hitting an iceberg near the South Shetland Islands. There are no fatalities.
events.html: • 2007 – MS Explorer, a cruise liner carrying 154 people, sinks in the Antarctic Ocean south of Argentina after hitting an iceberg near the South Shetland Islands. There are no fatalities.

events.description: The Maguindanao massacre occurs in Ampatuan, Maguindanao, Philippines; 58 opponents of Andal Ampatuan Jr. are kidnapped and killed.
events.html: • 2009 – The Maguindanao massacre occurs in Ampatuan, Maguindanao, Philippines; 58 opponents of Andal Ampatuan Jr. are kidnapped and killed.[18]

events.description: Bombardment of Yeonpyeong: North Korean artillery attack kills two civilians and two marines on Yeonpyeong Island, South Korea.
events.html: • 2010 – Bombardment of Yeonpyeong: North Korean artillery attack kills two civilians and two marines on Yeonpyeong Island, South Korea.[19]

events.description: Arab Spring: After 11 months of protests in Yemen, Yemeni president Ali Abdullah Saleh signs a deal to transfer power to the vice president, in exchange for legal immunity.
events.html: • 2011 – Arab Spring: After 11 months of protests in Yemen, Yemeni president Ali Abdullah Saleh signs a deal to transfer power to the vice president, in exchange for legal immunity.[20]

events.description: Blue Origin's New Shepard space vehicle became the first rocket to successfully fly to space and then return to Earth for a controlled, vertical landing.
events.html: • 2015 – Blue Origin's New Shepard space vehicle became the first rocket to successfully fly to space and then return to Earth for a controlled, vertical landing.[21]

events.description: Founders of Italian fashion brand Dolce & Gabbana issue an apology following a series of offensive advertisements on social media promoting a fashion show in Shanghai, China, which was canceled.
events.html: • 2018 – Founders of Italian fashion brand Dolce & Gabbana issue an apology following a series of offensive advertisements on social media promoting a fashion show in Shanghai, China, which was canceled.[22]

events.description: The last Sumatran rhinoceros in Malaysia, Imam, dies, making the species officially extinct in the country.
events.html: • 2019 – The last Sumatran rhinoceros in Malaysia, Imam, dies, making the species officially extinct in the country.[23]
